type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation documentation_summary: The HTML text is about the `types-aiobotocore-wisdom` package version 2.12.1, available on PyPI for installation. This package provides type annotations for the `aiobotocore.ConnectWisdomService` 2.12.1 service, generated with `mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2`. It is designed to be compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright, enhancing code completion and bug detection capabilities. The package requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. It supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.8 to 3.13 and is maintained by Vlad Emelianov. The package is production/stable and aims at developers, offering a comprehensive solution for working with `aiobotocore` services by providing explicit type annotations, client annotations, paginator annotations, literals, and type definitions for improved type checking and code quality.
